# demo-builder3 — photoreal 3D shirt rebuild (improve pass)

Replaced the procedural tube-and-cylinder shirt with an offline-authored garment
mesh + baked AO, rendered with PBR fabric materials. Owayo-style realism, Bowlifi
mock-neck quarter-zip silhouette (no pocket), full 360 orbit.

## what changed
- NEW tools/sculpt.mjs: deterministic garment authoring (runs ~4s). Analytic
  garment loft consumes true pattern fabric width per cross-section; front/back
  panels via Coons grids; sleeves lofted from the real armhole ring (arc-length
  UV parametrization); analytic-ring stand collar; yoke shrinkwrap onto a
  mannequin SDF; masked Laplacian relax at shoulders/caps; crafted displacement
  wrinkles (hang folds, armpit tension, zip channel, hem waves); welded seams w/
  pinch; hemisphere-raycast vertex AO; trim bands + zipper geometry; exports
  public/shirt.bin (custom packed binary, ~1.1MB).
- tools/drape.mjs (kept for reference): full PBD cloth sim w/ sewing —
  abandoned: unstable + slow (~90s chunked); sculpt is the supported path.
- lib/compositor.ts v2: clean panel atlas (front island x20..1006, back
  x1042..2028, y460..1769 as-seen/unmirrored; sleeves y24..424). Back images no
  longer mirrored-duplicated. backText now drawn into the atlas (arched) so it
  follows fabric + AO. wrap mode spans both body islands; mirrorSeam mirrors the
  back panel.
- lib/shirtMesh.ts: shirt.bin loader (AO -> vertex colors).
- components/ShirtCanvas.tsx: rewritten. Loads baked meshes; MeshPhysical fabric
  (compositor map, knit normal, sheen, AO); BackSide lining passes; local
  RoomEnvironment (replaces drei CDN HDR fetch — offline-safe); soft key light +
  contact shadow; damped autorotate orbit.
- tools/preview/index.html + tools/shot.mjs + tools/qa.mjs: headless render
  harness (swiftshader; one browser per view + retry).

## verification
- UV debug grid: FRONT/BACK upright + unmirrored, uniform texel density.
- qa.mjs against the built app: console errors NONE; color swatch, wrap upload,
  transforms all live on the new mesh.
- Deployed copy serves clean from michaelwegter.com/public/demos/bowling-shirt-designer.
- Card hero refreshed: public/work-samples/bowling-shirt-designer.png.

## handoff
- produced: baked garment asset pipeline (sculpt.mjs -> shirt.bin), rewritten
  renderer + compositor v2, deployed build + new card screenshot. Committed, NOT pushed.
- decisions: deterministic sculpt over cloth dynamics; panel-atlas UVs
  (unmirrored back) are the compositor contract — any mesh change must keep it.
- next needs: push both repos to go live; optional material polish (AO strength,
  knit scale) after seeing it on real hardware GPU.
- risks: stale hashed _next chunks from the old build remain in the site folder
  (sandbox cannot delete); harmless but prune on next Mac-side pass.
